s body and empowered by a lunar eclipse \u2013 strikes at him and breaks out of her prison within his dime. Meanwhile, Webby, Launchpad and Mrs. Beakley convince Donald and the boys to forgive Scrooge. Just then, Magica reveals herself to all of Duckburg and releases everyone's shadows. Joined by Gyro, Fenton, Little Bulb, and Manny the Headless Man-Horse, Donald - equipped with a voice box ([[Don Cheadle]]) - Mrs. Beakley and Launchpad fight back against Magica while the kids try to get Lena's assistance. At her home, they discover she's a shadow created by Magica and rush back to stop the sorceress. In the end, Lena seemingly sacrifices herself to save Webby before Magica is stripped of her magic and forced to flee. While Webby mourns for Lena, unaware she merged with her shadow, the family reunites while a newscast on their heroics is seen by Della ([[Paget Brewster]]), who's stranded on the Moon.\n |LineColor       = FFEF00\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 2 (2018\u201319)===\n{{Episode table|background=#F89E32|overall=5|season=5|title=15|director=9|writer=27|aux2=13|airdate=10|prodcode=7|viewers=9|country=U.S.|aux2T=Storyboard by|titleR=<ref name=WDTV>{{cite web|url=https://www.wdtvpress.com/disneychannel/shows/ducktales/episodes/|title=Walt Disney Television - DuckTales: Episode info|website=Walt Disney Television Press|accessdate=September 9, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"WDTV September\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wdtvpress.com/disneyxd/pressrelease/september-2019-programming-highlights-for-disney-channel-disney-xd-and-disney-junior|title=WDTV September}}</ref>|prodcodeR=<ref name=WDTV/>|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 24\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = The Most Dangerous Game...Night!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Emmy Cicierega & Ben Holm\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|201