chuck graduation, Huey and Violet must compete in a challenge to earn the title of Senior Woodchuck. Panicked by the possibility of losing, Huey begins hallucinating a talking Junior Woodchuck guidebook ([[Stephen Root]]) aiding him and ignoring Violet when she becomes endangered. After Violet in turn saves his life, he admits she is a better Woodchuck and forfeits the competition. During this time, Scrooge finds a map to the treasure of Isabella Finch, but his attempts to find it are thwarted when the rest of the family decide to chase a strange bird instead. While he insists they are missing out, the others remind him that it is more meaningful to have an adventure all your own than to follow someone else's example. The bird ultimately ends up leading them to Finch's treasure: her lost adventure journal, which contains a list of legendary treasures she was unable to find. The group resolve to hunt the treasures down, unaware that F.O.W.L. is spying on them and seeks the treasures as well.\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 49\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Quack Pack!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = Bob Snow\n |Aux2            = Kristen Gish\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|4}}\n |ProdCode        = \n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = While on an adventure to find the Lost Lamp of Collie Baba, Donald wishes for a normal life; unaware he was next to the lamp or that it contained [[List of DuckTales characters#Gene the Genie|Gene the Genie]] ([[Jaleel White]]). Fulfilling Donald's wish, Gene sends the family into a '90s sitcom called ''[[Quack Pack]]'' and erases their memories. While focusing on taking the perfect family photo, Huey suspects something's wrong after hearing Donald's voice and manages to convince the others once he discovers they're in a TV studio. Meanwhile, Donald tries his best to hide his secret by maintaining the plotline and reluctantly hiring his neighbor, [[Goofy]] ([[Bill Farmer]]), to be the photographer. After the family finds Gene however, he tells them only Donald can reverse the wish since he made it, but he refuses to and storms off with Goofy. When the others resolve to escape, the wish fights back to maintain itself. Using his son [[Max Goof|Max]] as inspiration, Goofy helps Donald realize \"normal\" can mean different things for different families before helping him save his. Amidst the chaos, Goofy finds the lamp and Donald uses his second wish to undo his first. With the last one, he gets a framed picture of him and his family.\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 50\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Double-O-Duck in You Only Crash Twice!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = Jason Zurek\n |WrittenBy       = Christian Magalhaes\n |Aux2            = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|11}}\n |ProdCode        = \n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = <!--No more than 200 words episode summary, written in your OWN words. Copy and pasting from Futon Critic / Walt Disney Television will be reverted as a copyright violation [[WP:COPYVIO]]-->\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 51\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = The Lost Harp of Mervana!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |Aux2            = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|18}}\n |ProdCode        = \n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = <!--No more than 200 words episode summary, written in your OWN words. Copy and pasting from Futon Critic / Walt Disney Television will be reverted as a copyright violation [[WP:COPYVIO]]-->\n|LineColor        = 960018\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 52\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Louie's Eleven!\n |RTitle          =\n |DirectedBy      = \n |WrittenBy       = \n |Aux2            = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|25}}\n |ProdCode   