e, Louie loses Scrooge's [[Number One Dime]] and decides to use [[Gyro Gearloose]]'s ([[Jim Rash]]) robotic light-bulb, [[Little Bulb]], to get it back. However, he causes it to become a giant coin-collecting robot, and is forced to stop him all on his own and retrieve the Dime before Scrooge notices. Meanwhile, Dewey and Webby face the McDuck Archives' dedicated keeper, [[Emily Quackfaster|Mrs. Quackfaster]] ([[Susanne Blakeslee]]), in order to gain information on Della and solve the mystery of her disappearance. In the end, they find a note from Della \u2013 \"Scrooge, I took ''The Spear of Selene,'' I'm sorry\" \u2013 and decide to keep this a secret until they know more. \n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = The Beagle Birthday Massacre!\n |DirectedBy      = Dana Terrace\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Emmy Cicierega, Ben Holm & Jason Reicher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|9|30}}\n |ProdCode        = 106\n |Viewers         = 0.38<ref>{{cite news|last1=Metcalf|first1=Mitch|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 9.30.2017|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-30-2017.html|accessdate=October 4, 2017|work=ShowBuzz Daily|date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109010944/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-9-30-2017.html|archivedate=January 9, 2018|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Disappointed after having to be left behind by the boys, Webby meets and bonds with a rebellious teen, Lena ([[Kimiko Glenn]]). The two inadvertently crash Ma Beagle's birthday party and are pursued by the whole Beagle clan. They and the boys, who were looking for Webby, are eventually captured, but they manage to escape and remain friends. Unbeknownst to the young ducks, Lena is revealed to be the niece of the evil sorceress, [[Magica De Spell]].\n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Terror of the Terra-firmians!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys & Tom Owens\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Magalhaes}}\n |Aux2            = David Baker, Owens, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|7}}\n |ProdCode        = 110\n |Viewers         = 0.39<ref>Metcalf, Mitch (Oct 10, 2017) [http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-7-2017.html UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.7.2017] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180203174128/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-7-2017.html |date=February 3, 2018 }} Showbuzzdaily.</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = After seeing a scary movie, Huey, Webby, and Lena explore an abandoned subway line in search of legendary creatures, [[Land Beneath the Ground!|the Terra-firmians]], only to end up trapped underground with Mrs. Beakley, Louie, Dewey, and Launchpad. As they struggle to escape, Launchpad becomes more and more paranoid, leaving Dewey to help him come back to his senses. Huey and Webby argue over the creatures' existence, as the former believes only in his [[Junior Woodchucks|Junior Woodchuck]] Guidebook and is afraid to do anything that doesn't follow its instructions. In the end however, the two reconcile and find out that the Terra-firmians are actually real. In the midst of their adventure, Lena struggles to gain Mrs. Beakley's trust while secretly receiving instructions from Magica ([[Catherine Tate]]).  \n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = The House of the Lucky Gander!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys & Tom Owens\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Magalhaes}}\n |Aux2            = Dalton E. Grant Jr., Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|10|14}}{{efn|name=oct14|On [[Disney XD (Canada)|Disney XD Canada]], the episodes \"The Infernal Internship of Mark Beaks!\" and \"The House of the Lucky Gander!\" aired in an inverted order, on October 14, 2017<ref>{{cite web|title=DISNEY XD CANADA October 14th listing|url=https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|website=TV Passport|publisher=TV Media Inc.|accessdate=16 October 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20171014132743/https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|archivedate=October 14, 2017|date=14 October 2017|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and October 21, 2017<ref>{{cite web|title=DISNEY XD CANADA October 21st listing|url=https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|website=TV Passport|publisher=TV Media Inc.|accessdate=21 October 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20171021195206/https://www.tvpassport.com/tv-listings/stations/disney-xd-canada/17172|archivedate=October 21, 2017|date=21 October 2017|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> respectively.}}\n |ProdCode        = 107\n |Viewers         = 0.34<ref>Metcalf, Mitch (Oct 17, 2017) [http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-14-2017.html UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.14.2017] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017201758/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-14-2017.html |date=October 17, 2017 }} Showbuzzdaily.</ref>\