d of Disney XD.}}\n |ProdCode        = 112\n |Viewers         = 1.09<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-4-2018.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.4.2018 \u2013 Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 7, 2018|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|accessdate=May 7, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Scrooge and his family are stuck on the Island of Ithaquack, home of the [[Greek gods]], where Dewey and Webby try to search for ''The Spear of Selene'' and uncover the mystery of Della's disappearance. However, Dewey struggles with the possibility that his mother may not have been a good person. They later find out that ''The Spear of Selene'' does not belong to [[Selene]] ([[Nia Vardalos]]), goddess of the Moon, who reveals that Della was a great person and friend. Meanwhile, Donald is dragged into a competition to settle a dispute between Scrooge and [[Zeus]] ([[Michael Chiklis]]). [[Hercules|Storkules]] ([[Chris Diamantopoulos]]), Zeus' son and an acquaintance of Donald's, encourages him to continue adventuring, even in spite of Della's disappearance. \n |LineColor       = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 11\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n |Title           = Beware the B.U.D.D.Y. System!\n |DirectedBy      = John Aoshima\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Angones}}\n |Aux2            = Benjamin Balistreri, Evon Freeman, Mark Garcia, Tanner Johnson & John Ramirez\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|11}}\n |ProdCode        = 114\n |Viewers         = 0.68<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-11-2018.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.11.2018&nbsp;\u2013 Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 14, 2018|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|accessdate=May 14, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Launchpad finally receives his driver's license and goes with Dewey to show Scrooge, who is busy with Gyro and his bumbling intern, [[Fenton Crackshell-Cabrera]] ([[Lin-Manuel Miranda]]). Meanwhile, Beaks unveils a new [[self-driving car]], so Launchpad challenges Beaks' invention to a race to prove that men are better than machines. Even though he loses, it's revealed that Beaks stole Gyro's robot technology, thanks to Fenton, who posted it on the internet. Launchpad and Fenton both lose their jobs and end up humiliated. But when Scrooge, Dewey, Gyro, and Beaks become trapped inside the self-driving car, it's up to Launchpad and Fenton to save them; with the latter using Gyro's top secret project, a cybernetic suit, to become the robotic superhero \"[[Gizmoduck]]\". In the end, Launchpad gets his job back and earns Scrooge's recognition, Gyro lets Fenton use his invention permanently, and Beaks plots to get Gizmoduck for his own company. \n|LineColor        = FFEF00\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 12\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 12\n |Title           = The Missing Links of Moorshire!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Ben Joseph, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Joseph}}\n |Aux2            = Vaughn Tada, Brandon Warren & Jason Zurek\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|18}}{{efn|name=ep113|This episode made its broadcast premiere on [[Disney XD (Scandinavia)|Disney XD Scandinavia]] on March 21, 2018.}}\n |ProdCode        = 113\n |Viewers         = 0.87<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-18-2018.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.18.2018&nbsp;\u2013 Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 21, 2018|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|accessdate=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummar