s-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-20-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.20.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=October 23, 2018|access-date=October 23, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Tired of the constant adventuring, Louie attempts to avoid another one by proposing a family game night, causing Scrooge's competitive nature to kick in. Meanwhile, Gyro discovers a species of miniature people \u2013 the \"Gyropudlians\" \u2013 living at McDuck Manor and invented a shrink-ray to make contact with them. However, Louie panics and uses the shrink-ray on Gyro to silence him. He then convinces Huey to help him keep the others in the dark about the increasingly hostile Gyropudlians, but things escalate during a game of \"Scroogeopoly\". In the end, Louie steps up and saves the day, gaining Scrooge's respect.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 25\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = The Depths of Cousin Fethry!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Magalhaes}}\n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Vaughn Tada, Brandon Warren & Jason Zurek\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|10|27}}\n |ProdCode        = 202\n |Viewers         = 0.60<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-27-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 10.27.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=October 30, 2018|access-date=October 30, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Huey and Dewey have Launchpad take them to visit Donald's oddball cousin, [[Fethry Duck]] ([[Tom Kenny]]), whom they believe is a scientist working at one of Scrooge's marine stations. However, they eventually realize he's just the station's caretaker and turn to leave, only to be attacked by a sea monster. After Huey calms the creature by singing to it, Fethry realizes it's actually his pet [[krill]], Mitzi, who was mutated by hydro-thermal vents. Upon reaching the surface, Fethry decides to become a real scientist and leaves with Mitzi. The boys then meet up with Launchpad, who had his own undersea adventure.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 26\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = The Ballad of Duke Baloney!\n |DirectedBy      = Jason Zurek \n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Evanson}}\n |Aux2            = Jean-Sebastien Duclos, Sam King & Mike Morris\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|3}}\n |ProdCode        = 203\n |Viewers         = 0.52<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-11-3-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 11.3.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=November 6, 2018|access-date=November 6, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Glomgold has been missing for four months, during which time he is replaced by Zan Owlson ([[Natasha Rothwell]]) as his company's CEO. He is found with amnesia by fishermen, Fisher and Mann ([[John DiMaggio]] & [[Grey Griffin]]), and adopts a new identity as the fisherman \"Duke Baloney\". Louie and Webby stumble upon him and investigate, only for the mystery to deepen when they discover that \"Glomgold\" is a fake identity. They then take Scrooge to meet him, but he decides to let him be, as he is happy. However, Glomgold ultimately regains his memory: born \"Duke Baloney\"; he was a shoeshine boy who did Scrooge's shoes and was paid with a dime to teach him self-reliance, only for him to feel cheated and create his \"Glomgold\" persona to get revenge. He then returns to his company and makes a bet with Scrooge: whoever's richer by the end of the year gets the loser's company.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 27\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = The Town Where Everyone Was Nice!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Emmy Cicierega & Ben Holm\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|10}}\n |ProdCode        = 204\n |Viewers         = 0.55<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-11-10-2018.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 11.10.2018|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=November 13, 2018|access-date=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The family visits a Brazilian town to celebrate the mysterious festival, \"The Feast of the Flower\". While there, Donald reunites with his old college buddies, [[Jos\u00e9 Carioca]] and [[Panchito Pistoles]] (Bernardo de Paula & [[Arturo Del Puerto]]). Finding that they each live a successful life however, Donald pretends to be a billionaire to impress them, with Scrooge and Huey playing along. Meanwhile, Webby tries to get Dewey and Louie to fully experience the festival, but they just want to take pictures. They all soon discover that the town's friendly locals are all part of a giant [[carnivorous plant]]. After Donald tells the truth, and learns that his friends also lied, [[The Three Caballeros]] reunite to fight the plant with music.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 28\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Storkules in Duckburg!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Snow}}\n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|17}}