as, except for Scrooge and Dewey. In actuality though, Scrooge secretly goes back in time every Christmas to revisit his best parties with the [[Ghost of Christmas Past|Ghosts of Christmas Past]] ([[Jack McBrayer]]), [[Ghost of Christmas Present|Present]] ([[Bill Fagerbakke]]), and [[Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come|Future]]. However, he eventually realizes the real fun of Christmas is spending it with family. Past, on the other hand, doesn't want to let go of their fun times together and traps him in time, but Scrooge outsmarts him and escapes. Meanwhile Dewey, who secretly followed Scrooge to the past, ends up facing a [[wendigo]] with a younger Donald ([[Russi Taylor]]) and Della. They manage to capture it, after which it's revealed to be Past. Scrooge, who arrives to take Dewey back, then makes up with Past and they all return to the present to spend Christmas with the others. Meanwhile on the Moon, Della gives everyone her best wishes as she continues to fix her spaceship.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 30\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n |Title           = What Ever Happened To Della Duck?!\n |DirectedBy      = Tanner Johnson\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s= Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes & Bob Snow|t=Bateman & Evanson}}\n |Aux2            = Vince Aparo, Emmy Cicierega & Ben Holm\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|3|9}}\n |ProdCode        = 207\n |Viewers         = 0.61<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-9-2019.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.9.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=March 12, 2019|access-date=March 12, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Ten years ago, after losing contact with Scrooge during her flight, Della crash-lands on the Moon. Now with a robotic leg and Gyro's Oxy-Chew gum \u2013 which provides oxygen, water, and nutrients \u2013