 Magic!\n |DirectedBy      = Matthew Humphreys\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Francisco Angones, Madison Bateman, Colleen Evanson, Christian Magalhaes, Bob Snow & Rachel Vine|t=Vine}} \n |Aux2            = Stephanie Gonzaga, Victoria Harris, Vaughn Tada & Brandon Warren\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start Date|2019|5|15}}{{efn|name=ep214|This episode made its broadcast premiere on [[Disney Channel (Dutch TV channel)|Disney Channel Netherlands]] on April 28, 2019.}}\n |ProdCode        = 208\n |Viewers         = 0.33<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-wednesday-cable-originals-network-finals-5-15-2019.html|title=Top 150 Wednesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 5.15.2019|work=Showbuzz Daily|author=Mitch Metcalf|date=May 16, 2019|access-date=May 16, 2019}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Webby heads to the library to once again find a way to get Lena back from the Shadow Realm. While there, she meets another supernatural enthusiast, Violet Sabrewing ([[Libe Barer]]), who suggests they have a sleepover to further discuss said realm. Amidst the sleepover, Lena gets suspicious of Violet, learns she brought Magica's amulet, and tries to warn Webby. While trying to bring Lena back, Webby and Violet enter the Shadow Realm, where Webby briefly reunites with Lena before she's captured by [[tulpa]]s manifested from Lena's jealousy towards Violet. Together, Lena and Violet ward off the spirits, but this causes Lena to fade away too. Through the combined magic of Magica's amulet and Webby's friendship bracelet, Lena's brought back to the mortal world. The three girls become friends, with Lena warming up to Violet. Meanwhile, Mrs. Beakley desperately tries to befriend Launchpad after finding that she has no friends, and ends up bonding with him over ''[[Darkwing Duck]]''.\n |LineColor       = F89E32\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 38\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n |Title           = The Dangerous Chemistry of Gandra Dee!\n |DirectedBy