{"title_page": "Tawny Kitaen", "text_new": "{{short description|Actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Tawny Kitaen\n| image =\n| imagesize =\n| caption = Tawny Kitaen\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1961|08|05}}\n| birth_place = [[San Diego]], California, US\n| birthname = Julie E. Kitaen\n| occupation = Actress, comedian\n| yearsactive = 1979\u2013present\n| othername =\n| homepage =\n| spouse = [[David Coverdale]] (1989\u20131991)<br />[[Chuck Finley]] (1997\u20132002)\n| children = 2\n}}\n\n'''Julie E.''' \"'''Tawny'''\" '''Kitaen''' (born August 5, 1961) is an American actress, comedian and media personality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/38574/Tawny-Kitaen|work=[[The New York Times]]|title=Tawny Kitaen}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nTawny Kitaen was born in [[San Diego]], [[California]], in 1961, the daughter of Linda Kitaen (n\u00e9e Taylor), a housewife and a former beauty pageant participant, and Terry Kitaen, an employee of a [[neon sign]] company.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uWGr2sb_uvgC&pg=PA264&dq=%22Kitaen+wasn't+what+she+appeared+to+be+on+screen+and+in+the+sexy+rock+videos%22&hl=en|title=Seinfeld|publisher=|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref> Julie began using the nickname \"Tawny\" at the age of 12 on her own initiative.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/dyn/Celebrity_rehab_2_with_dr_drew/144585/episode_about.jhtml |title=Celebrity Rehab 2 with Dr. Drew &#124; Show Cast, Episodes, Guides, Trailers, Web Exclusives, Previews |publisher=VH1.com |date= |accessdate=2011-01-29}}</ref>\n\n==Acting career==\nKitaen began her acting career in 1983 with a minor role in the [[television movie]] ''[[Malibu (film)|Malibu]].'' In 1984, she starred as the title character of the erotic-adventure movie ''[[The Perils of Gwendoline in the Land of the Yik-Yak]],'' also called ''Gwendoline.'' She also co-starred in the movie ''[[Bachelor Party (1984 film)|Bachelor Party]]'' as the bride-to-be of [[Tom Hanks]]\u2019 character, and starred in the 1986 horror movie ''[[Witchboard]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/03/15/movies/love-triangle-in-witchboard.html|title=LOVE TRIANGLE IN 'WITCHBOARD'|work=The New York Times|first=Caryn|last=James|date=March 15, 1987}}</ref> She also starred in the 1997 movie \"Dead Tides\" with wrestler [[Roddy Piper]].\n\nKitaen appeared in several videos in the 1980s for the band [[Whitesnake]], including the hits \"[[Here I Go Again]]\", \"[[Still of the Night (song)|Still of the Night]]\",  \"[[Is This Love (Whitesnake song)|Is This Love]],\" and \"[[The Deeper the Love]]\". She was briefly married to Whitesnake's lead singer, [[David Coverdale]].\n\nKitaen appeared in ''[[Seinfeld]]'' as [[Jerry Seinfeld (character)|Jerry]]\u2019s girlfriend in the 1991 episode \"[[The Nose Job]]\".\n\nShe had recurring parts in ''[[Hercules: The Legendary Journeys]]'' and co-hosted ''[[America's Funniest People]]'' from 1992 to 1994.\n\nKitaen was also in 19 episodes of the TV series ''[[The New WKRP in Cincinnati]]'' from 1991 to 1993 as a night-time DJ named Mona Loveland; in the show, her night-time program was called ''Mona Til Midnight.''\n\n==Reality TV==\nKitaen was one of the cast of the sixth edition of the VH1 reality television show ''[[The Surreal Life]],'' which began airing in March 2006. Kitaen also appeared in the second season of the VH1 reality TV show ''[[Celebrity Rehab with Dr. Drew]],'' which began in October 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.earthtimes.org/articles/show/vh1-heads-back-to-rehab,427561.shtml|title= VH1 Heads Back to Rehab With Dr. Drew Pinsky for a Second Season of 'Celebrity Rehab With Dr. Drew'|date= June 10, 2008|work=EarthTimes.org}}</ref><ref name=TVGuide>''TV Guide,'' June 23, 2008; Page 8</ref><ref name=\"CelebCheck\">{{cite web|url= http://blog.vh1.com/2008-06-10/new-slate-of-celebs-check-into-rehab-2-with-dr-drew/|title= \"Celebs Check Into Rehab 2 With Dr. Drew\"|work=VH1.com|date=June 10, 2008|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080613005309/http://blog.vh1.com/2008-06-10/new-slate-of-celebs-check-into-rehab-2-with-dr-drew/|archivedate= June 13, 2008}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKitaen dated [[Ratt]] guitarist [[Robbin Crosby]] during and after high school. She followed the band to Los Angeles in the late 1970s to pursue a career of her own. Kitaen married Whitesnake singer [[David Coverdale]] in 1989. Coverdale and Kitaen divorced in 1991. Kitaen had an affair with [[O.J. Simpson]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.apnews.com/d6d0ac24e31e09deeb5ca1684fefe49e |title=Surprise letter: Nicole wrote O.J. Simpson 'beat holy hell' out of her |last=Deutsch |first=Linda |author-link=Linda Deutsch |date=13 January 1997 |publisher=[[The Associated Press]] |access-date=28 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nKitaen was married to baseball player [[Chuck Finley]] from 1997 to 2002. In 2002, she was charged with [[domestic violence]] for an incident involving Finley, whom she had kicked in the face repeatedly with high-heeled shoes.<ref name=\"people2002\">{{Cite web |last=Silverman |first=Stephen M. |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,624669,00.html |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |title=Kitaen Files $12-Mil Lawsuit Against Ex |date=September 24, 2002}}</ref> Three days later, Finley filed for divorce.<ref name=\"people2002\" /> After a [[plea bargain]], Kitaen agreed to \"enter a spousal battery counseling program and avoid contact with Finley.\"<ref name=\"people2002\" /> The couple had been married for five years and had two daughters together.<ref>{{Cite news |url = http://www.cbc.ca/sports/story/2002/09/18/kitaen020918.html |title=Wife accepts Chuck Finley plea bargain |website=cbcsports |date=September 18, 2002}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2006, prosecutors charged Kitaen with possessing 15&nbsp;grams of [[cocaine]] in her [[San Juan Capistrano]] home in [[Orange County, California|Orange County]]. The authorities said her two children were home at the time and Kitaen had given deputies permission for the search.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tawny Kitaen Faces Felony Drug Charges|website=[[CBS News]]|date=November 22, 2006|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2006/11/22/entertainment/main2206915.shtml|last=Faber|first=Judy|accessdate=December 31, 2008}}</ref> In December 2006, she entered a six-month rehabilitation program in exchange for the dismissal of a [[felony]] [[drug possession]] charge.<ref name=msnbc>{{Cite web|url=http://www.msn.com/|title=MSN &#124; Outlook, Office, Skype, Bing, Breaking News, and Latest Videos|website=www.msn.com}}</ref><ref>Vyas, Sunil; [http://www.earthtimes.org/articles/show/10823.html 'Bachelor Party' actress Tawny Kitaen in cocaine possession row] earthtimes.org; November 23, 2006</ref><ref>Reuters; [https://www.today.com/news/tawny-kitaen-enters-drug-rehab-cocaine-wbna16273369 Tawny Kitaen enters drug rehab for cocaine] msnbc; December 18, 2006</ref>\n\nOn September 26, 2009, Kitaen was arrested for [[driving under the influence]] in [[Newport Beach, California]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5gAkvAPv2q1OD0cadi8eSlVDwtuUQD9AVCOOO6|title=Actress Tawny Kitaen arrested in Calif. for DUI|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date = September 26, 2009}}</ref> The following July, she pleaded [[no contest]] to misdemeanor DUI and was sentenced to {{Citation needed span|text=a couple of days|reason=Define \"a couple of days\" as a judge would legally order. I'm unable to correct text due to the citation at the end of this paragraph being unavailable owing to website maintenance; said Cite News template has a seemingly unrelated title.|date=April 2020}} in jail, ordered to attend a first-offender alcohol program, and required to perform 64&nbsp;hours of community service.<ref name=\"Homes\">{{cite news|last1=Coker|first1=Matt|title=Tawny Kitaen Sells 2 Homes for $4.3&nbsp;Million, Which Is Less Than What She Paid for Them|url=http://www.ocweekly.com/news/tawny-kitaen-sells-2-homes-for-43-million-which-is-less-than-what-she-paid-for-them-6479835|accessdate=11 August 2017|date=4 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[The Perils of Gwendoline in the Land of the Yik-Yak]]''\n|Gwendoline\n|\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[Bachelor Party (1984 film)|Bachelor Party]]''\n|Debbie Thompson\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Witchboard]]''\n|Linda Brewster\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''Crystal Heart''\n|Alley Daniels\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Instant Justice]]''\n|Virginia\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''Happy Hour''\n|Misty Roberts\n|\n|-\n|1989\n|''White Hot''\n|Vanessa\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Three of Hearts (1993 film)|Three of Hearts]]''\n|Woman in Bar\n|\n|-\n|1996\n|''Playback''\n|Sara Burgess\n|\n|-\n|1997\n|''Dead Tides''\n|Nola\n|\n|-\n|2002\n|''Happy Hour''\n|\n|Short film\n|-\n|2009\n|''Too Cool''\n|\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''Here We Go Again''\n|\n|Short film\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[After Midnight (2014 film)| After Midnight]]''\n|Rikki\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1976\n|''[[To Tell the Truth]]''\n|Herself\n|Game show\n|-\n|1983\n|''[[Malibu (film)|Malibu]]''\n|Mahoney's girlfriend\n|TV film\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[California Girls (film)|California Girls]]''\n|Karen Malone\n|TV film\n|-\n|1986-1987\n|''[[Capitol (TV series)|Capitol]]''\n|Meredith Ross\n|TV series\n|-\n|1987\n|''Glory Years''\n|Melinda Murphy\n|TV film\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Santa Barbara (TV series)|Santa Barbara]]''\n|Lisa DiNapoli\n|Appeared between February 28, 1989 and July 21, 1989<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://santabarbara-online.com/lisadin2.htm|title=Lisa DiNapoli|website=santabarbara-online.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://capridge.com/lisa.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150223203744/http://capridge.com/lisa.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 23, 2015|title=Lisa DiNapoli - Santa Barbara|date=February 23, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Booker (TV series)|Booker]]''\n|Skylar Samperton\n|Episode: \"Someone Stole Lucille\"\n|-\n|1991\n|''They Came From Outer Space''\n|Monica Bates\n|Episode: \"Sex, Lies & UFOs: Part 2\"\n|-\n|1991\n|''[[Shades of L.A.]]''\n|Linda Makowski\n|Episodes: \"Line of Fire: Parts 1 & 2\"\n|-\n|1991\n|''Veronica Clare''\n|\n|Episodes: \"The Boxing Story\", \"Slow Violence\"\n|-\n|1991\n|''[[Seinfeld]]''\n|Isabel\n|Episode: \"The Nose Job\"\n|-\n|1991-1993\n|''{{sortname|The|New WKRP in Cincinnati}}''\n|Mona Loveland\n|Main role (19 episodes)\n|-\n|1992-1994\n|''[[America's Funniest People]]''\n|Co-host\n|Succeeded [[Arleen Sorkin]]\n|-\n|1992-1996\n|''[[Eek! The Cat]]''\n|Annabelle (voice)\n|Main role (39 episodes)\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Married... with Children]]''\n|Dominique\n|Episode: \"Shoeway to Heaven\"\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Hercules and the Circle of Fire]]''\n|Deianeira\n|TV film\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Hercules in the Underworld]]''\n|Deianeira\n|TV film\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Hercules in the Maze of the Minotaur]]''\n|Deianeira\n|TV film\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Burke's Law (1994 TV series)|Burke's Law]]''\n|Rhonda Dooley\n|Episode: \"Who Killed Cock-a-Doodle Dooley?\"\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Hercules: The Legendary Journeys]]''\n|Deianeira\n|Episodes: \"[[The Wrong Path]]\", \"[[The Other Side (Hercules: The Legendary Journeys)|The Other Side]]\"\n|-\n|1997\n|''[[Hercules: The Legendary Journeys]]''\n|Deianeira\n|Episode: \"[[When a Man Loves a Woman (Hercules: The Legendary Journeys)|When a Man Loves a Woman]]\"\n|-\n|2006\n|''[[The Surreal Life#Season 6|The Surreal Life]]''\n|Herself\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]''\n|Lydia Kole\n|Episode: \"Father of the Bride\"\n|-\n|2012\n|''Life@Large''\n|\n|TV miniseries\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Botched (TV series)|Botched]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode Boob Trains and Big Butts\n|}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|478}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kitaen, Tawny}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from San Juan Capistrano, California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from San Diego]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Tawny Kitaen\n| image =\n| imagesize =\n| caption = Tawny Kitaen\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1961|08|05}}\n| birth_place = [[San Diego]], California, US\n| birthname = Julie E. Kitaen\n| occupation = Actress, comedian\n| yearsactive = 1979\u2013present\n| othername =\n| homepage =\n| spouse = [[David Coverdale]] (1989\u20131991)<br />[[Chuck Finley]] (1997\u20132002)\n| children = 2\n}}\n\n'''Julie E.''' \"'''Tawny'''\" '''Kitaen''' (born August 5, 1961) is an American actress, comedian and media personality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/38574/Tawny-Kitaen|work=[[The New York Times]]|title=Tawny Kitaen}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nTawny Kitaen was born in [[San Diego]], [[California]], in 1961, the daughter of Linda Kitaen (n\u00e9e Taylor), a housewife and a former beauty pageant participant, and Terry Kitaen, an employee of a [[neon sign]] company.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uWGr2sb_uvgC&pg=PA264&dq=%22Kitaen+wasn't+what+she+appeared+to+be+on+screen+and+in+the+sexy+rock+videos%22&hl=en|title=Seinfeld|publisher=|accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref> Julie began using the nickname \"Tawny\" at the age of 12 on her own initiative.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/dyn/Celebrity_rehab_2_with_dr_drew/144585/episode_about.jhtml |title=Celebrity Rehab 2 with Dr. Drew &#124; Show Cast, Episodes, Guides, Trailers, Web Exclusives, Previews |publisher=VH1.com |date= |accessdate=2011-01-29}}</ref>\n\n==Acting career==\nKitaen began her acting career in 1983 with a minor role in the [[television movie]] ''[[Malibu (film)|Malibu]].'' In 1984, she starred as the title character of the erotic-adventure movie ''[[The Perils of Gwendoline in the Land of the Yik-Yak]],'' also called ''Gwendoline.'' She also co-starred in the movie ''[[Bachelor Party (1984 film)|Bachelor Party]]'' as the bride-to-be of [[Tom Hanks]]\u2019 character, and starred in the 1986 horror movie ''[[Witchboard]].''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/03/15/movies/love-triangle-in-witchboard.html|title=LOVE TRIANGLE IN 'WITCHBOARD'|work=The New York Times|first=Caryn|last=James|date=March 15, 1987}}</ref> She also starred in the 1997 movie \"Dead Tides\" with wrestler [[Roddy Piper]].\n\nKitaen appeared in several videos in the 1980s for the band [[Whitesnake]], including the hits \"[[Here I Go Again]]\", \"[[Still of the Night (song)|Still of the Night]]\",  \"[[Is This Love (Whitesnake song)|Is This Love]],\" and \"[[The Deeper the Love]]\". She was briefly married to Whitesnake's lead singer, [[David Coverdale]].\n\nKitaen appeared in ''[[Seinfeld]]'' as [[Jerry Seinfeld (character)|Jerry]]\u2019s girlfriend in the 1991 episode \"[[The Nose Job]]\".\n\nShe had recurring parts in ''[[Hercules: The Legendary Journeys]]'' and co-hosted ''[[America's Funniest People]]'' from 1992 to 1994.\n\nKitaen was also in 19 episodes of the TV series ''[[The New WKRP in Cincinnati]]'' from 1991 to 1993 as a night-time DJ named Mona Loveland; in the show, her night-time program was called ''Mona Til Midnight.''\n\n==Reality TV==\nKitaen was one of the cast of the sixth edition of the VH1 reality television show ''[[The Surreal Life]],'' which began airing in March 2006. Kitaen also appeared in the second season of the VH1 reality TV show ''[[Celebrity Rehab with Dr. Drew]],'' which began in October 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.earthtimes.org/articles/show/vh1-heads-back-to-rehab,427561.shtml|title= VH1 Heads Back to Rehab With Dr. Drew Pinsky for a Second Season of 'Celebrity Rehab With Dr. Drew'|date= June 10, 2008|work=EarthTimes.org}}</ref><ref name=TVGuide>''TV Guide,'' June 23, 2008; Page 8</ref><ref name=\"CelebCheck\">{{cite web|url= http://blog.vh1.com/2008-06-10/new-slate-of-celebs-check-into-rehab-2-with-dr-drew/|title= \"Celebs Check Into Rehab 2 With Dr. Drew\"|work=VH1.com|date=June 10, 2008|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080613005309/http://blog.vh1.com/2008-06-10/new-slate-of-celebs-check-into-rehab-2-with-dr-drew/|archivedate= June 13, 2008}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKitaen dated [[Ratt]] guitarist [[Robbin Crosby]] during and after high school. She followed the band to Los Angeles in the late 1970s to pursue a career of her own. Kitaen married Whitesnake singer [[David Coverdale]] in 1989. Coverdale and Kitaen divorced in 1991. Kitaen had an affair with [[O.J. Simpson]]. <ref>{{cite web \n | url = https://www.apnews.com/d6d0ac24e31e09deeb5ca1684fefe49e\n | title = Surprise letter: Nicole wrote O.J. Simpson \u2018beat holy hell\u2019 out of her\n | date = January 13, 1997\n | author = [[Linda Deutsch]]\n | publisher = [[The Associated Press]]\n | accessdate = October 28, 2019}}\n</ref>\n\nKitaen was married to baseball player [[Chuck Finley]] from 1997 to 2002. In 2002, she was charged with [[domestic violence]] for an incident involving Finley, whom she had kicked in the face repeatedly with high-heeled shoes. <ref name=\"people2002\">{{cite web|first=Stephen M.|last=Silverman|url = http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,624669,00.html|magazine= [[People (magazine)|People]]|title = Kitaen Files $12-Mil Lawsuit Against Ex|date = September 24, 2002}}</ref> Three days later, Finley filed for divorce.<ref name=\"people2002\" /> After a [[plea bargain]], Kitaen agreed to \"enter a spousal battery counseling program and avoid contact with Finley.\"<ref name=\"people2002\" /> The couple had been married for five years and had two daughters together.<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.cbc.ca/sports/story/2002/09/18/kitaen020918.html|title = Wife accepts Chuck Finley plea bargain|website = cbcsports|date = September 18, 2002}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2006, prosecutors charged Kitaen with possessing 15&nbsp;grams of [[cocaine]] in her [[San Juan Capistrano]] home in [[Orange County, California|Orange County]]. The authorities said her two children were home at the time and Kitaen had given deputies permission for the search.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tawny Kitaen Faces Felony Drug Charges|website=[[CBS News Online]]|date=November 22, 2006|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2006/11/22/entertainment/main2206915.shtml|last=Faber|first=Judy|accessdate=December 31, 2008}}</ref> In December 2006, she entered a six-month rehabilitation program in exchange for the dismissal of a [[felony]] [[drug possession]] charge.<ref name=msnbc>{{Cite web|url=http://www.msn.com/|title=MSN &#124; Outlook, Office, Skype, Bing, Breaking News, and Latest Videos|website=www.msn.com}}</ref><ref>Vyas, Sunil; [http://www.earthtimes.org/articles/show/10823.html 'Bachelor Party' actress Tawny Kitaen in cocaine possession row] earthtimes.org; November 23, 2006</ref><ref>Reuters; [https://www.today.com/news/tawny-kitaen-enters-drug-rehab-cocaine-wbna16273369 Tawny Kitaen enters drug rehab for cocaine] msnbc; December 18, 2006</ref>\n\nOn September 26, 2009, Kitaen was arrested for [[driving under the influence]] in [[Newport Beach, California]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5gAkvAPv2q1OD0cadi8eSlVDwtuUQD9AVCOOO6|title=Actress Tawny Kitaen arrested in Calif. for DUI|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date = September 26, 2009}}</ref> The following July, she pleaded [[no contest]] to misdemeanor DUI and was sentenced to {{Citation needed span|text=a couple of days|reason=Define \"a couple of days\" as a judge would legally order. I'm unable to correct text due to the citation at the end of this paragraph being unavailable owing to website maintenance; said Cite News template has a seemingly unrelated title.|date=April 2020}} in jail, ordered to attend a first-offender alcohol program, and required to perform 64&nbsp;hours of community service.<ref name=\"Homes\">{{cite news|last1=Coker|first1=Matt|title=Tawny Kitaen Sells 2 Homes for $4.3&nbsp;Million, Which Is Less Than What She Paid for Them|url=http://www.ocweekly.com/news/tawny-kitaen-sells-2-homes-for-43-million-which-is-less-than-what-she-paid-for-them-6479835|accessdate=11 August 2017|date=4 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[The Perils of Gwendoline in the Land of the Yik-Yak]]''\n|Gwendoline\n|\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[Bachelor Party (1984 film)|Bachelor Party]]''\n|Debbie Thompson\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Witchboard]]''\n|Linda Brewster\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''Crystal Heart''\n|Alley Daniels\n|\n|-\n|1986\n|''[[Instant Justice]]''\n|Virginia\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''Happy Hour''\n|Misty Roberts\n|\n|-\n|1989\n|''White Hot''\n|Vanessa\n|\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[Three of Hearts (1993 film)|Three of Hearts]]''\n|Woman in Bar\n|\n|-\n|1996\n|''Playback''\n|Sara Burgess\n|\n|-\n|1997\n|''Dead Tides''\n|Nola\n|\n|-\n|2002\n|''Happy Hour''\n|\n|Short film\n|-\n|2009\n|''Too Cool''\n|\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''Here We Go Again''\n|\n|Short film\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[After Midnight (2014 film)| After Midnight]]''\n|Rikki\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1976\n|''[[To Tell the Truth]]''\n|Herself\n|Game show\n|-\n|1983\n|''[[Malibu (film)|Malibu]]''\n|Mahoney's girlfriend\n|TV film\n|-\n|1985\n|''[[California Girls (film)|California Girls]]''\n|Karen Malone\n|TV film\n|-\n|1986-1987\n|''[[Capitol (TV series)|Capitol]]''\n|Meredith Ross\n|TV series\n|-\n|1987\n|''Glory Years''\n|Melinda Murphy\n|TV film\n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Santa Barbara (TV series)|Santa Barbara]]''\n|Lisa DiNa